{"id":253,"parent_id":245,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":253,"title":"1 Samuel 8","subtitle":"","short_title":"1 Sam.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 8"],[".studySummary",["i","Samuel’s sons take bribes and pervert judgment—The Israelites seek for a king to rule over them—Samuel rehearses the nature and evils of kingly rule—The Lord consents to give them a king."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.1","order":"02.10.008.21062"},["b","1"],"And it came to pass, when",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"Samuel"],"was old, that he made his sons judges over Israel."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.2","order":"02.10.008.21063"},["b","2"],"Now the name of his firstborn was Joel; and the name of his second, Abiah:",["i","they were"],"judges in Beer-sheba."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.3","order":"02.10.008.21064"},["b","3"],"And his sons walked not in his ways, but turned aside after lucre, and took",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"bribes"],", and perverted judgment."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.4","order":"02.10.008.21065"},["b","4"],"Then all the elders of Israel gathered themselves together, and came to Samuel unto Ramah,"],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.5","order":"02.10.008.21066"},["b","5"],"And said unto him, Behold, thou art old, and thy sons",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"walk"],"not in thy ways: now make us a",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_5b"},"king"],"to judge us like all the nations."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.6","order":"02.10.008.21067"},["b","6"],"¶But the thing displeased Samuel, when they said, Give us a king to judge us. And Samuel prayed unto the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.7","order":"02.10.008.21068"},["b","7"],"And the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"said unto Samuel, Hearken unto the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"voice"],"of the people in all that they say unto thee: for they have not rejected thee, but they have",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_7b"},"rejected"],"me, that I should not",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_7c"},"reign"],"over them."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.8","order":"02.10.008.21069"},["b","8"],"According to all the works which they have done since the day that I brought them up out of Egypt even unto this day, wherewith they have forsaken me, and served other gods, so do they also unto thee."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.9","order":"02.10.008.21070"},["b","9"],"Now therefore hearken unto their voice: howbeit yet",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_9a"},"protest"],"solemnly unto them, and shew them the manner of the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_9b"},"king"],"that shall",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_9c"},"reign"],"over them."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.10","order":"02.10.008.21071"},["b","10"],"¶And Samuel told all the words of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"unto the people that asked of him a king."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.11","order":"02.10.008.21072"},["b","11"],"And he said, This will be the manner of the king that shall reign over you: He will take your sons, and appoint",["i","them"],"for himself, for his chariots, and",["i","to be"],"his horsemen; and",["i","some"],"shall run before his chariots."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.12","order":"02.10.008.21073"},["b","12"],"And he will appoint him captains over thousands, and captains over fifties; and",["i","will set them"],"to",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"ear"],"his ground, and to reap his harvest, and to make his instruments of war, and instruments of his chariots."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.13","order":"02.10.008.21074"},["b","13"],"And he will take your daughters",["i","to be"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"confectionaries"],", and",["i","to be"],"cooks, and",["i","to be"],"bakers."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.14","order":"02.10.008.21075"},["b","14"],"And he will take your fields, and your vineyards, and your oliveyards,",["i","even"],"the best",["i","of them,"],"and give",["i","them"],"to his servants."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.15","order":"02.10.008.21076"},["b","15"],"And he will take the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"tenth"],"of your seed, and of your vineyards, and give to his officers, and to his servants."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.16","order":"02.10.008.21077"},["b","16"],"And he will take your menservants, and your maidservants, and your goodliest young men, and your asses, and put",["i","them"],"to his work."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.17","order":"02.10.008.21078"},["b","17"],"He will take the tenth of your sheep: and ye shall be his servants."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.18","order":"02.10.008.21079"},["b","18"],"And ye shall cry out in that day because of your",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_18a"},"king"],"which ye shall have",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_18b"},"chosen"],"you; and the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"will not",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_18c"},"hear"],"you in that day."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.19","order":"02.10.008.21080"},["b","19"],"¶Nevertheless the people refused to",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_19a"},"obey"],"the voice of Samuel; and they said, Nay; but we will have a king over us;"],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.20","order":"02.10.008.21081"},["b","20"],"That we also may be like all the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_20a"},"nations"],"; and that our king may judge us, and go out before us, and fight our battles."],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.21","order":"02.10.008.21082"},["b","21"],"And Samuel heard all the words of the people, and he rehearsed them in the ears of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"."],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.22","order":"02.10.008.21083"},["b","22"],"And the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"said to Samuel, Hearken unto their voice, and make them a king. And Samuel said unto the men of Israel, Go ye every man unto his city."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.1a","order":"02.10.008.21084"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/6.28"},"1 Chr. 6:28"],"."],["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.3a","order":"02.10.008.21086"},["b","3a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/18.21.20-22"},"Ex. 18:21 (20–22)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.20"},"Hel. 9:20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/9.11"},"Ether 9:11"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.5a","order":"02.10.008.21088"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/walking-in-darkness"},"TG Walking in Darkness"],"."],["div",{"id":"5b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.5b","order":"02.10.008.21090"},["b","5b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/hosea/13.10.9-14"},"Hosea 13:10 (9–14)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.6.6-13"},"Mosiah 23:6 (6–13)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/29.16.10-39"},"29:16 (10–39)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/6.30"},"3 Ne. 6:30"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/38.21"},"D&C 38:21"],"."],["div",{"id":"7a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.7a","order":"02.10.008.21092"},["b","7a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/29.26"},"Mosiah 29:26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/29.4"},"Alma 29:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/26.2"},"D&C 26:2"],"."],["div",{"id":"7b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.7b","order":"02.10.008.21094"},["b","7b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/16.8"},"Ex. 16:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/hosea/13.11"},"Hosea 13:11"],";",["a.scrip